    "body": "### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n```\r\n# do in in a view\r\nroot_url \r\nroot_url(subdomain: 'test')\r\n```\r\n### Expected behavior\r\nHole rails application lives on subdomain ex.: `https://rails.example.com`\r\nI'm trying to generate a link on subdomain and expect to have a link in 3rd level subdomian\r\n```\r\n  root_url # => https://rails.example.com\r\n  root_url(subdomain: 'test') # => https://test.rails.example.com\r\n```\r\n### Actual behavior\r\nBut helper removes main subdomain instead\r\n```\r\n  root_url # => https://rails.example.com\r\n  root_url(subdomain: 'test') # => https://test.example.com\r\n```\r\nSame issue with `*_url` to different routes\r\n### System configuration\r\n**Rails version**: 5.1.6\r\n\r\n**Ruby version**: 2.5.1\r\n"
