    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nRun this script https://gist.github.com/alimi/169f192784c69383272c1258cba65759. The tests with `non_unicode_string` will raise the exception.\r\n\r\nRun https://gist.github.com/alimi/b8071867f4611a54eb9647ac5d0241a4 to verify it works on 5.2.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nBefore Rails 6, `String#parameterize` and the underlying methods it calls supported non-Unicode strings. Maybe they still should in Rails 6?\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n`String#parameterize` and the underlying methods it calls no longer support non-Unicode strings. They now raise `Encoding::CompatibilityError`s.\r\n\r\nIt looks like the change in behavior was introduced in https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/26743. `String#parameterize` eventually calls `ActiveSupport::Unicode::Multibyte#normalize`. `#normalize` [used to do a bunch of stuff](https://github.com/rails/rails/blob/fc5dd0b85189811062c85520fd70de8389b55aeb/activesupport/lib/active_support/multibyte/unicode.rb#L274) and now it's [mostly a wrapper around the native Ruby method](https://github.com/rails/rails/blob/cf608ee34dd833b0357ef4eefa692db33242d2aa/activesupport/lib/active_support/multibyte/unicode.rb#L108).\r\n\r\n### System configuration\r\n**Rails version**: master\r\n\r\n**Ruby version**: 2.5.0p0\r\n\r\n/cc @eileencodes @rafaelfranca @mtsmfm\r\n"
