    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Vanilla ActiveStorage `has_one_attached` file setup using disk storage locally\r\n2. Add `direct_upload: true` for file field like so:\r\n```erb\r\n<%= form_with model: import_file do |form| %>            \r\n  <div class=\"form-group\">                               \r\n    <%= form.label :file, %>            \r\n    <%= form.file_field :file, direct_upload: true, required: true %>                                  \r\n  </div>                                                 \r\n<% end %>\r\n```\r\n3. Gzip a file of any size e.g. `gzip my_file.csv`\r\n4. Upload file via the file input                      \r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\nDirect upload should process like any other file\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\nGet a `422` Unprocessable entity on a subsequent `PUT` request to the ActiveStorage controller. Regular file uploads work and direct uploads work if they are in any other format besides gzipped.\r\n\r\n### System configuration\r\n**Rails version**: 5.2.1\r\n**Ruby version**: 2.5\r\n"
