    "pull_request": {
      "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/pulls/34033",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/34033",
      "diff_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/34033.diff",
      "patch_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/34033.patch"
    },
    "body": "### Summary\r\n\r\nThis PR fixes https://github.com/rails/rails/issues/33991.\r\n\r\nWhen you have has_one/has_many through association like below.\r\n\r\n``` .rb\r\nclass Invoice < ApplicationRecord\r\n    has_many :invoice_lines\r\nend\r\n\r\nclass InvoiceLine < ApplicationRecord\r\n    belongs_to :invoice\r\n    belongs_to :job\r\nend\r\n\r\nclass Job < ApplicationRecord\r\n    has_one :invoice_line\r\n    has_one :invoice, through: :invoice_line\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\nQuery with association behave wrongly.\r\n\r\n``` .rb\r\nJob.joins(:invoice).where(invoice: Invoice.last).to_sql\r\n=> \"SELECT \\\"jobs\\\".* FROM \\\"jobs\\\" INNER JOIN \\\"invoice_lines\\\" ON \\\"invoice_lines\\\".\\\"job_id\\\" = \\\"jobs\\\".\\\"id\\\" INNER JOIN \\\"invoices\\\" ON \\\"invoices\\\".\\\"id\\\" = \\\"invoice_lines\\\".\\\"invoice_id\\\" WHERE \\\"jobs\\\".\\\"id\\\" IS NULL\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is because `through` association `predicate_builder.rb` doesn't care association is `through` or not.\r\nSo, it try to get `invoices.invoice_id # => nil`. That's why this sql will has `jobs.id IS NULL'.\r\n\r\nI changed `predicate_builder.rb` to care `through` association and build sql.\r\n\r\nAfter change, the sql statement will be like this.\r\n\r\n``` .rb\r\nJob.joins(:invoice).where(invoice: Invoice.last).to_sql\r\n=> \"SELECT \\\"jobs\\\".* FROM \\\"jobs\\\" INNER JOIN \\\"invoice_lines\\\" ON \\\"invoice_lines\\\".\\\"job_id\\\" = \\\"jobs\\\".\\\"id\\\" INNER JOIN \\\"invoices\\\" ON \\\"invoices\\\".\\\"id\\\" = \\\"invoice_lines\\\".\\\"invoice_id\\\" WHERE \\\"invoices\\\".\\\"id\\\" = 121\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nTo fix this, I add methods(`association_through_reflection?`, `table_name`, `primary_key`) to `table_metadata.rb`.\r\nIf it has better way, please give me advices.\r\n"
